HEADWORD: Nosophen
<hw>Nos"o*phen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Nose</ets> +
<ets>phenol</ets>; orig. used for affections of the nose.]</ety>
<fld>(Pharm.)</fld> <def>An iodine compound obtained as a yellowish
gray, odorless, tasteless powder by the action of iodine on
phenolphthalein.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

